Pneumatophore : The pneumatophore (
Fig. 12 A
) was very distinctive and measured 5.5 mm in height and 2.1 mm in diameter. There was a group of darker cells at its apex, which may indicate that it was pigmented in life, and eight external ribs that petered out toward the apex. The pneumatosaccus was restricted to a small volume in the apical half. It was not clear, however, how much distortion occurred due to the expansion of gas during retrieval.

Nectosome : The young nectophoral buds were attached below the pneumatophore on the ventral side of the stem (
Fig. 12 A
).
